The laboratory studies showed a moderate microcytic hypochrome anemia with a hemoglobin level of 8,6 g/dL, a normal leukocyte and platelet count. Routine biochemical tests evidenced a mild hypoproteinemia of 5,9 g/dL and hypoalbuminemia of 3,3 g/dL, a low ionized serum calcium of 3,2 mg/dL and a decreased level of circulating iron of 35 Î¼g/dL. The other biochemical results were within normal ranges. The urine examination was normal, without urine protein loss. 